issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
- When i run the code bellow to get content of a japanese website. so the console log will print the text result with some broken character.

- The problem happened when i call function text (res.text()).
- After look at code of function `async text()`. i saw that the problem is toString function that will convert buffer to string with encoding is `UTF-8`. But the correct encoding in my case is `shift_jis`

```js
/**
* Decode response as text
*
* @return  Promise
*/
async text() {
  const buffer = await consumeBody(this);
  return buffer.toString(); // <= toString function will convert buffer to string with encoding is UTF-8. But the correct encoding in my case is shift_jis
}
```

* My script
```js
const fetch = require('node-fetch');

fetch(
  'https://www.leopalace21.com/apps/tradeCondition/logonAction.do;jsessionid=0001W7h94kP1CI4B8v272KUswNN:17abad7vp?fbclid=IwAR3rHpV6wO6-cqW7d7YM7W-J7mcOyDxTYP57EjgLy19K-yV737k0dT4yUdo',
  {
    body: null,
    method: 'GET',
    mode: 'cors',
  },
)
  .then((res) => res.text())
  .then((text) => {
    console.log(text);
  });


```

* My result
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7193344/126626078-8bfcd679-87f6-41d9-9635-3f234c59b881.png)


**Describe the solution you'd like**

So i think we must convert buffer to string with correct encoding instead of just toString().
- The first step will be detect original encoding of buffer
- The second step will be convert original to utf-8 encoding

Or to be friendly we should provide some useful parameter to `async text()` like `autodetectEncoding = true`, destinationEncoding with default value is `UTF-8`

Let see my temp solution
```js
const fetch = require('node-fetch');

fetch(
  'https://www.leopalace21.com/apps/tradeCondition/logonAction.do;jsessionid=0001W7h94kP1CI4B8v272KUswNN:17abad7vp?fbclid=IwAR3rHpV6wO6-cqW7d7YM7W-J7mcOyDxTYP57EjgLy19K-yV737k0dT4yUdo',
  {
    referrerPolicy: 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin',
    body: null,
    method: 'GET',
    mode: 'cors',
  },
)
  .then((res) => res.buffer())
  .then((buffer) => {
    const decoder = new TextDecoder('shift_jis');
    const r = decoder.decode(buffer);
    console.log(r);
  });

```
Result
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7193344/126627191-0ce79fdb-0afb-48b6-a42b-c5b7387fc2bc.png)

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
Solution to detect buffer encoding `https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byte_order_mark` 
[my demo](https://gist.github.com/anhdiepmmk/53dee3789c987db8c9bd6b5f9956d4fc)
or to be faster you can use this npmjs lib [detect-character-encoding](https://www.npmjs.com/package/detect-character-encoding)

